Scalia and Thomas have lunch with health care law opponents while the court is hearing the case.
On the day the Supreme Court convened behind closed doors to discuss the politically controversial question of whether it would hear President Obama's health care bill, two of its justices, Antonin Scalia and Clarence Thomas, were celebrating a lunch sponsored by the law firm that will be challenging the case before the Supreme Court.
This case occurred last Thursday when all nine judges met to discuss the petitions before the court.
