"While military funding in the Overseas Emergency Operations is not directly affected by the sequester, military achievements will be severely affected by a major disruption in the core budgets", Panetta warned.
"Contract staff will be cut, ending with the cancellation of contracts and the supervision contract that supports the troops".
"Staff will be cut, which will lead to delays in payments to military suppliers, and legal and political support will be disrupted".
