"Sequestration is a threat to the national security interests of the United States, and it cannot be allowed to happen".
Whether Panetta's letter or the Senators' recent warnings will lead to a budget compromise or intensify calls for the Pentagon to be relieved of the cuts, we'll see later.
Panetta was absolutely sincere about the potential cuts, even though he came to work at the Pentagon after years of budgetary scrutiny in Congress and the White House and realizing he was facing a tough choice.
