President Álvaro Colom said Tuesday that the extradition process for Alfonso Portillo has begun, so that he can answer in the United States for a $70 million money laundering conspiracy.
This is the end of the process by which Guatemala responded to a request from a northern country that demanded Portillo's extradition to stand trial there.
